HEADWORD: Acetonemia
<hw>Ac`e*to*ne"mi*a</hw></mhw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See <er>Acetone</er>;
<er>H⟦ae⟧ma-</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A morbid condition
characterized by the presence of ketone bodies (including acetone,
acetoacetic acid and beta-hydroxybutyric acid) in the blood, as in
diabetes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

